0.2 Matriz

porcentaje edges positivos (pep) : En el paper reportan edges negativos 70% para sujeto A y 63% para B. Usar 10% de pep, para que no me salgan tan altos & sea error.

conectance (c): Usar el 0.05, valor ms cercano para food network & dentro del rango inferido para microbial net.

#N: No. de especies 
N = 10 
pep = 10
conec = 0.05

A = generateA(N,"klemm", pep = pep, c = conec)

0.3 Modelos

0.3.1 Modelos del Artculo de Faust

0.3.1.1 Ricker

Revisar lo de K, en el artculo dice que la capacidad de carga es una distribucin uniforme de 0 a 0.5.

#tiempo
tend = 15
#noise, trmino de fuerza
sigm = c(0.01,0.05,0.1)
#capacidad de carga
cap = 0.01

for (sig in sigm) {
  rickerplot=tsplot(ricker(N,A=A,K=rep(cap,N), tend=tend, sigma = sig), main = paste("Ricker", "%ep =", pep, "c =", conec, " =", sig, "K =", cap), legend = TRUE ) 
}

GUARDAR setwd("~/Microtesis/Tesis1/03.OUTPUT/PLOTS/RICKER/")

RData save(rickerplot, file = paste("Ricker", "N =", N, "Tiempo = ", tend, "pep =", pep, "c =", conec, "sigma =", sig, "K =", cap,".RData"))

PDF pdf(paste("Ricker", "N =", N, "Tiempo = ", tend, "pep =", pep, "c =", conec, "sigma =", sig, "K =", cap, ".pdf"))

0.3.1.2 gLV

tend = 1.5
grmin = 0
grmax = 0.5


glvplot=tsplot(glv (N, A=A, tend=tend, b = runif(N, min = grmin, max = grmax)), main = paste("gLV", "%ep =", pep, "c =", conec, "tasa crecimiento", grmin, "-", grmax), legend = TRUE )

GUARDAR setwd("~/Microtesis/Tesis1/03.OUTPUT/PLOTS/gLV/")

RData save(glvplot, file = paste("gLV", "N =", N, "Tiempo = ", tend, "pep =", pep, "c =", conec, "tasa crecimiento", grmin, "-", grmax,".RData"))

PDF pdf(paste("gLV", "N =", N, "Tiempo = ", tend, "pep =", pep, "c =", conec, "tasa crecimiento", grmin, "-", grmax, ".pdf"))
